    <bioghist>Pinckney, Michigan physician and businessman, and member of the board of directors of the Michigan Air Line Railroad Company.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Family correspondence, including letter, 1850, discussing a trek to California to join the gold rush; correspondence and other documents, 1868-1890, detailing role in the management, financing, and construction of the Michigan Air Line Railroad; scattered records, 1856-1866, of Broughton, Haze &amp; Wilcox, Pinckney, Michigan, investment and money-lending firm; collected papers, 1880-1884, relating to litigation over the Pinckney public square; and miscellaneous later family documents.</scopecontent>
